name: textile production, cotton, air jet loom weaving | textile, woven cotton | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/20185/documentation

Inventory refers to the weaving of 1 kg  yarn (450 GSM) into textile, the production of the yarn itself is not included. The dataset is extrapolated from the respective Indian dataset. For detailed information regarding technology please refer to the aforementioned datasets.;[This dataset is meant to replace the following datasets:]

The activity starts with warping and sizing of cotton yarn.

This process ends with conversion of cotton yarn at weaving plant to 1 kg of woven fabric.
category: C:Manufacturing/13:Manufacture of textiles/131:Spinning, weaving and finishing of textiles/1312:Weaving of textiles

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Global average based on data from India.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Dataset extrapolated to correspond to global conditions.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Dataset is extrapolated from the respective Indian dataset. Uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Industry data. Representative mills in Haryana (North India) was chosen to provide data based on its technical representativeness of the current state of business and their willingness to participate.
